1. State Machines — Transiciones Validas e Ilegales
Cada entidad que tiene 'status' necesita una state machine. Sin esto, el developer va a permitir transiciones imposibles.
1.1 Invoice / Factura
DRAFT -> SENT          // enviar al cliente
DRAFT -> CANCELLED     // cancelar antes de enviar
SENT -> VIEWED         // cliente abrio el link (automatico)
SENT -> PAID           // pago completo recibido
SENT -> PARTIAL        // pago parcial
SENT -> OVERDUE        // paso la fecha de vencimiento (CRON automatico)
SENT -> CANCELLED      // cancelar factura enviada (requiere motivo)
VIEWED -> PAID
VIEWED -> PARTIAL
VIEWED -> OVERDUE
VIEWED -> CANCELLED
OVERDUE -> PAID        // pago tardio
OVERDUE -> PARTIAL
OVERDUE -> CANCELLED
PARTIAL -> PAID        // completar pago
PARTIAL -> OVERDUE
PARTIAL -> CANCELLED

ILEGALES (NUNCA permitir):
PAID -> cualquier estado (final - inmutable)
CANCELLED -> cualquier estado (final - inmutable)
SENT -> DRAFT (no se puede des-enviar)
OVERDUE -> DRAFT

CFDI ADICIONAL (Mexico):
STAMPED -> CANCEL_REQUESTED  // solicitar cancelacion ante SAT
CANCEL_REQUESTED -> CANCELLED // SAT acepta cancelacion
CANCEL_REQUESTED -> STAMPED   // SAT rechaza cancelacion (receptor no acepto)

1.2 Shipment / Envio (Cargo)
CONFIRMED -> DRIVER_ASSIGNED -> DRIVER_EN_ROUTE -> PICKED_UP
PICKED_UP -> IN_WAREHOUSE_USA -> IN_CONTAINER -> IN_TRANSIT_INTERNATIONAL
IN_TRANSIT_INTERNATIONAL -> ARRIVED_PORT -> IN_CUSTOMS -> RELEASED
RELEASED -> IN_WAREHOUSE_DEST -> DRIVER_ASSIGNED_DELIVERY -> OUT_FOR_DELIVERY -> DELIVERED

EXCEPCIONES (desde cualquier estado pre-delivery):
ANY_PRE_DELIVERY -> EXCEPTION  // problema (cliente no esta, danado, direccion incorrecta)
EXCEPTION -> estado_anterior   // resuelto, volver al flujo normal
EXCEPTION -> RETURNED          // devolver al remitente

ILEGALES:
DELIVERED -> cualquiera (final)
RETURNED -> cualquiera (final)
IN_TRANSIT -> PICKED_UP (no retroceder)
IN_WAREHOUSE_DEST -> IN_WAREHOUSE_USA (no retroceder entre paises)

1.3 Deal / Oportunidad CRM
LEAD -> CONTACTED -> QUALIFIED -> PROPOSAL -> NEGOTIATION -> WON
                                                           -> LOST

Cualquier etapa -> LOST (puede perderse en cualquier momento)
LOST -> LEAD (reabrir oportunidad perdida - registrar motivo)
WON -> genera evento deal.won -> FACTURA crea factura draft

ILEGALES:
WON -> LOST (si ya gano, no puede perder - usar nota de credito)
LEAD -> WON (no puede saltar etapas - debe pasar por al menos PROPOSAL)

1.4 Ticket Soporte
OPEN -> ASSIGNED -> IN_PROGRESS -> WAITING_CUSTOMER -> RESOLVED -> CLOSED
WAITING_CUSTOMER -> IN_PROGRESS (cliente responde)
RESOLVED -> REOPENED -> IN_PROGRESS (cliente no satisfecho)
ANY -> CLOSED (cerrar forzado por admin despues de 30 dias inactivo)

SLA: si OPEN sin ASSIGNED por 2 horas -> alerta a supervisor
SLA: si IN_PROGRESS sin respuesta por 24 horas -> alerta a manager
SLA: WAITING_CUSTOMER por 7 dias sin respuesta -> auto-RESOLVED

1.5 Expense Report / Reporte de Gastos
DRAFT -> SUBMITTED -> APPROVED -> REIMBURSED
SUBMITTED -> REJECTED (manager rechaza, empleado debe corregir)
REJECTED -> DRAFT (empleado corrige y re-envia)
APPROVED -> REIMBURSED (pago procesado)

ILEGALES: REIMBURSED -> cualquiera (ya se pago, si hay error -> nota credito)

1.6 Purchase Order / Orden de Compra
DRAFT -> PENDING_APPROVAL -> APPROVED -> SENT_TO_VENDOR -> PARTIALLY_RECEIVED -> RECEIVED -> BILLED
PENDING_APPROVAL -> REJECTED -> DRAFT (corregir y re-enviar)
APPROVED -> CANCELLED (cancelar antes de enviar al proveedor)
SENT_TO_VENDOR -> CANCELLED (cancelar con penalidad posible)

1.7 Payroll / Nomina
DRAFT -> CALCULATING -> REVIEW -> APPROVED -> PAID
REVIEW -> DRAFT (errores encontrados, recalcular)
APPROVED -> PAID (dispersar pagos + timbrar CFDIs nomina en MX)
PAID es FINAL. Si hay error: generar nomina complementaria.

Implementacion Tecnica
// state-machine.ts - Motor de transiciones para TODA la plataforma

const MACHINES = {
  invoice: {
    DRAFT: ['SENT', 'CANCELLED'],
    SENT: ['VIEWED', 'PAID', 'PARTIAL', 'OVERDUE', 'CANCELLED'],
    VIEWED: ['PAID', 'PARTIAL', 'OVERDUE', 'CANCELLED'],
    OVERDUE: ['PAID', 'PARTIAL', 'CANCELLED'],
    PARTIAL: ['PAID', 'OVERDUE', 'CANCELLED'],
    PAID: [],      // terminal
    CANCELLED: [], // terminal
  },
  shipment: { /* ... */ },
  deal: { /* ... */ },
  ticket: { /* ... */ },
  expense: { /* ... */ },
  purchase_order: { /* ... */ },
  payroll: { /* ... */ },
};

function canTransition(entity: string, from: string, to: string): boolean {
  return MACHINES[entity]?.[from]?.includes(to) ?? false;
}

function transition(entity: string, record: any, newStatus: string, userId: string) {
  if (!canTransition(entity, record.status, newStatus)) {
    throw new Error(`Transicion ilegal: ${record.status} -> ${newStatus}`);
  }
  const oldStatus = record.status;
  record.status = newStatus;
  record.updated_at = new Date();
  // Audit log
  auditLog({ entity, id: record.id, from: oldStatus, to: newStatus, by: userId });
  // Emitir evento al Event Bus
  eventBus.emit(`${entity}.status_changed`, { id: record.id, from: oldStatus, to: newStatus });
}

